Analysis¶

After the data wrangling process, i was able to clean up the data and store the clean data in a my local computer as a csv file named "Twitter_archive_master.csv". This data was futher imported and used in conducting analysis where the following insights were discovered and proper visualisations was created to back each insights.

Insights:¶

  1. Doggo have Higher favorite counts compared to other dogs stages

  2. The algorithm of prediction is more confident on P1_dogs predictions compared to P2 and P3 dogs predictions

  3. There is positive correlation between favorite counts and retweet counts

  4. Pupper dogs have the highest valid ratings compared to other dog stages

  5. The Dogs with the mean highest ratings appears to be the Doggos and not the Puppers

    For the first insight i observed that doggos appeared to accumulate more favorite counts compared to other dogs.This is properly illustrated using the visuals below

The Diagram above shows that the doggo stage dogs have more favourite counts all summed up compared to every other dag stages, despite it being the second most populated dog stage in the data set. We can from the Diagram that doggo has a total of approximately 95,000 favourite counts, Puppo approx 35,000, Pupper approx. 30,000 and floofer approx. 20,000 favorite counts.

For the Second insight it appeared that the confidence levels are higher for the p1_dogs predictions compared to any other predictions in the dataset.This is illustrated in the diagram below.

From the above diagram, the Green histogram is the distribution of the P3_confidence level, the Yellow histogram is the Distribution of the P2_confidence level and the Blue histogram is the distribution of the P1_confidence level, hence we can observe that that P2 and P3 confidence levels are centered across 0-0.5 while for p1 we have values raging from 0-1.0 with most of its predictions having confidence levels close to one, this is an indicator that P1 have Dogs predictions that have higher confidence levels compared to other predictions.

For the Third insight, I observed the existence of a strong positive correlation between retweet counts and favorite counts in the data set, This is further illustrated in the diagram below.

From the Scatterplot above we can observe the upward trend in the data points relating favorite counts and retweet counts, which is a good indicator of a positive correlation between these two variables.
